div.div:
Isolation:
If each user query is run in its own thread, there is no isolation, not even Read Uncommitted. In fact, there is no transaction, since it's impossible to abort & revert.
Alternative 1: Because `put one`, `get one`, and `get range` are atomic, if we removed support for RMW, then we would have Serializable isolation.
Alternative 2: If we run queries serially, we have Serializable isolation. Then, we would have only two threads: a) queries runner, b) GC job.
Locking order:
To avoid deadlocks, always lock "top" first, then "bottom" (or always vice versa).
